content:
October 20, 1973, All in the Family's "lovable bigot" Archie Bunker finally met his next-door neighbor, the equally prejudiced George Jefferson. Bunker, played by Carroll O'Connor, and Jefferson, portrayed by Sherman Hemsley, remain two of television's most recognizable characters.
On January, 18, 1975, less than two years after George's first appearance on All in the Family, the Jeffersons would "move on up" to their own long-running spinoff series, The Jeffersons.
